          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target wheel consisted of nine arc-shaped targets",
                "with a nominal areal density of ~460 microg/cm2 208Pb",
                "metal on 35 microg/cm2 natC. A thin <10 microg/cm2",
                "layer of natC was applied to the downstream side of",
                "the targets to improve infrared cooling and prevent",
                "target material loss. The target wheel rotation speed",
                "was 5-10 Hz."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWPC",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detection system used consists of a",
                "multiwire proportional counter upstream of the FPD.",
                "The FPD is constructed with a five-sided box geometry",
                "from 58 mm x 58 mm 300 microm-thick Si-strip detector",
                "cards, each with 16 strips. The focal plane of the",
                "BGS is made of three cards totaling 48 strips."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ASPEC",
                "REC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The BGS separates out evaporation residues",
                " (EVRs) from unreacted beam and undesirable reaction",
                "products by their differing magnetic rigidities in",
                "dilute He gas. Cross sections were deduced from the",
                "count of alpha-decay chains. Of the five alpha decays",
                "of 266Mt observed in these experiments, only two",
                "registered a full-energy signal in the FPD."
              ]
            }
          ],
